Global Funds Buy Net 36.7 Million Rupees of Indian Derivatives

-- B y   P a r e s h   J a t a k i a
-- 
2011-06-28T04:03:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-28/global-funds-buy-net-36-7-million-rupees-of-indian-derivatives.html
Global investors bought a net 36.7
million rupees ($815,600) of Indian equity  derivatives 
yesterday, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, rose 1.3 percent to 1 trillion rupees, or 33.1
percent of the gross market position, according to the
exchangeâ€™s website. Open interest reached a record 1.6 trillion
rupees on Sept. 21.  Foreign funds bought a net 14.5 billion rupees of shares in
the  cash  segment yesterday, according to preliminary data given
by the bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
